I"Æ<p>When building a <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/memory-palace-makes-spaced-repetition-physical">memory palace</a>, the topology of the <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/conversational-interfaces-render-knowledge-bases-into-agents">knowledge base</a> being <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/linear-transformations-are-perfectly-described-by-matrices">projected</a> onto <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/spaces-can-be-interfaces">physical space</a> has to be close to the <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/brains-are-like-buildings">architecture</a> of the actual <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/cloud-anchors-are-like-place-cells">place</a>. Connected <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/concepts-are-like-rooms">rooms</a> can be nodes in a <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/knowledge-graph-connectivity-quantifies-knowledge-work">graph</a>. <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/spatial-reasoning-is-the-confluence-of-all-senses">Spatial</a> and various <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/working-memory-recruits-sensory-areas-for-housing-representations">sensorial</a> <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/curse-of-dimensionality-hinders-high-dimensional-mappings">dimensions</a> can house the projection of a <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/latent-spaces-have-both-continuous-and-discrete-properties">latent space</a>. <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/fragmentation-granularity-fosters-mixing-in-tea-and-societies">Representation granularity</a> and abstract switching layers can help <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/alignment-is-reflexive-symmetric-and-transitive">align</a> the two.</p>
